    {
      "heading": "Install Node.js",
      "level": 3,
      "slug": "install-nodejs",
      "prose": "Node.js® is a JavaScript runtime built on Chrome's V8 JavaScript engine. Node.js is required in order to run the Davur build tools. Download the latest version of Node and install it: nodejs.org/en/download/",
      "tables": [],
      "lists": [],
      "code_blocks": [],
      "links": []
    },
    {
      "heading": "Update your NPM",
      "level": 3,
      "slug": "update-your-npm",
      "prose": "Npm is the package manager for JavaScript and the world’s largest software registry. Npm is a separate project from Node.js, and tends to update more frequently. As a result, even if you’ve just downloaded Node.js (and therefore npm), you’ll probably need to update your npm.\n\n```sh\nnpm install --global npm@latest\n```",
      "tables": [],
      "lists": [],
      "code_blocks": [
        {
          "lang": "sh",
          "value": "npm install --global npm@latest\n"
        }
      ],
      "links": []
    },
    {
      "heading": "Install all dependencies",
      "level": 3,
      "slug": "install-all-dependencies",
      "prose": "If you want to update or develop this theme, you need to install all dependencies by running:\nWindows:\n\n```sh\nnpm install\n```",
      "tables": [],
      "lists": [],
      "code_blocks": [
        {
          "lang": "sh",
          "value": "npm install\n"
        }
      ],
      "links": []
